The <b>DPA 4006</b> is a high-quality small-diaphragm omnidirectional [[condenser microphone]] with an exceptionally flat frequency response (±2dB 15Hz - 20kHz). It comes in two forms - the original 4006 has a transformer-based preamplifier, while the 4006-TL is of a transformerless design. The microphone is powered by 48v phantom power and the polar pattern can be altered acoustically by using grids and mounted elements provided with the microphone. 


